name: Bases Loaded '96: Double Header
overview: Bases Loaded '96: Double Header is a Baseball Sim game, developed and published by Jaleco Entertainment, which was released in 1995. This game was the eighth and final game in the Bases Loaded series and the only one developed internally by Jaleco, after TOSE had developed the previous seven installments. Negative reviews were given to this game for its graphics and inappropriate choice of organ music.
